Hi! 👋
I have several miners in the network, and I noticed that the OTF validator does not distribute requests evenly among them.

For example, my oldest miner (UID 232) has been active for 21 hours, but hasn’t received a single request from OTF. Meanwhile, my other miners (UID 68, 59, 210) do receive requests from the validator. So, the validator itself is working, but the distribution looks incorrect.

Additionally, I noticed that the top validator sends a request to miner only once every ~17 hours. As a result, during the entire immunity period, the validator manages to make only two requests:
1. The first request – sending the task.
2. The second request – fetching the result of the first task.

After that, the immunity period ends, and the validator doesn’t have enough time to send a second task and fetch its result. And this is only in the best-case scenario, when the validator sends the first request immediately after we start the miner – which almost never happens.

It’s also important to note that the first requests come with low difficulty, since the validator still needs time to learn which tasks are optimal for the miner. As a result, during the entire immunity period, we effectively get only two requests, and they are often not very useful.

Proposed solutions from me –  we see two possible ways to address this issue:
1. Fix the validator behavior so that requests are distributed more evenly among miners
2. Increase the immunity period to at least 15,000 blocks, so that miners have enough time to receive and process more valuable tasks

## Update V1.2.5

Leading up to the Shors release, we wanted to make a healthier ecosystem for new miners. This update includes the following:

- Reduction in total scoring time from 48h to 36h
- Quicker start-up for new miners, allowing them to get up to speed before the end of immunity period. Their score will now be divided by the time they have been on the subnet; i.e. if a miner has been around for 18h, their score will be doubled since they have only had half as much time to compete
- The immunity period will soon be reduced from 15,000 blocks to 11,500 blocks
- We have seen miners get knocked off by mass registrations, and are trying to limit the potential for this to happen as we lead into Shors
- We have also increased the incentive pool by 5% as we continue to plan for new challenges in the public sphere, outside of the Bittensor ecosystem (the "Ridges approach")

Miners do not need to pull these changes

We discovered an error when scaling a new miners score. Validators would include past scores for an immune miner, when they had a different UID but the same hotkey.
